+{"_type":"issue","id":"mindspec-3cfr","title":"[bug] mindspec adr show/list read the main worktree only, inconsistent with adr create + worktree-aware validator (GH #145.2/.3)","description":"GitHub issue #145 (points #2 and #3). adr show/list resolve via workspace.FindRoot (-\u003e main repo root), so editing an ADR in the active spec WORKTREE does not change `mindspec adr show` output, while `mindspec adr create` (FindLocalRoot) writes to the worktree. This split made the reporter edit ADR-0001 repeatedly thinking the Domain(s) parse was broken (point #3) — but it was the main-vs-worktree split: they edited the worktree copy, adr show read main (empty).\n\nVERIFIED on main:\n- cmd/mindspec/adr.go: adr show (~L138) and adr list (~L97) use workspace.FindRoot (main); adr create (~L32) uses workspace.FindLocalRoot (worktree). The plan VALIDATOR is already worktree-aware (adrStoreForSpec, fixed in ew79) — so the gate works; only the inspection CLIs are main-only.\n- Point #3: internal/adr/parse.go (~L74) strings.Contains accepts BOTH `**Domain(s)**:` and `- **Domain(s)**:`, so parsing is NOT actually format-sensitive — but there is no test for the non-list form and templates only emit the list form.\n\nFIX: make adr show/list resolve from the active worktree (overlay like the validator), or clearly document/emit that ADRs are main-worktree-global. Add a parse test for the non-list `**Domain(s)**:` form to lock current behavior. Domains: cli/adr (+ adr).","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"richardmaxsteel@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-15T16:58:58Z","created_by":"mrmaxsteel","updated_at":"2026-06-15T16:58:58Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
